Interface ObservableListListener<E extends javafx.beans.Observable>

  • Type Parameters:

    All Superinterfaces:

    public interface ObservableListListener<E extends javafx.beans.Observable>
extends ListListener<E>
    Represents an entity that listen to changes either to a list structure (added and removed elements) and to the elements via the Observable interface which must be implemented by the elements.

    • Method Detail

      • onElementsChanged

        void onElementsChanged(java.util.List<? extends E> es)
        Called when elements are updated in the list.

        The changes to the list's elements are detected via the Observable interface which is implemented by the elements.

        If multiple items are updated at the same time (e.g. with List.replaceAll(UnaryOperator) this method is called just once for all the elements.

        Parameters:
        es - the changed elements
